IgG4-related sclerosing disease: autoimmune pancreatitis and extrapancreatic manifestations. Autoimmune pancreatitis is the pancreatic manifestation of IgG4-related sclerosing disease, which recently was recognized as a distinct disease entity. Numerous extrapancreatic organs, such as the bile ducts, gallbladder, kidneys, retroperitoneum, thyroid, salivary glands, lung, mediastinum, lymph nodes, and prostate may be involved, either synchronously or metachronously. Most cases of autoimmune pancreatitis are associated with elevated serum IgG4 levels extensive IgG4-positive plasma cells